  <static seed="1341" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/multiplyRationalExpressions20.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{18\mathopen{}\left(y+t\right)}{y-t}} \cdot {\frac{y-t}{6\mathopen{}\left(3y+t\right)}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(y+t\right)}{3y+t}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We cancel the factor <m>(y-t)</m> and reduce the fraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{18\mathopen{}\left(y+t\right)}{y-t}} \cdot {\frac{y-t}{6\mathopen{}\left(3y+t\right)}} \amp = {\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(y+t\right)}{3y+t}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Note that we may not further reduce <m>{\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(y+t\right)}{3y+t}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
